# Troubleshooting Workflows

These workflows outline the structured approach used to diagnose and resolve the issues in this project.
They demonstrate methodical troubleshooting and alignment with standard IT support practices.

---

##  Password Reset / Account Lockout
1. Verify user's identity
2. Check AD account status
3. Unlock account
4. Reset password
5. Force password change at next login
6. Confirm successful login

---

##  VPN Authentication Failure
1. Confirm network/internet connection
2. Validate authentication method (MFA)
3. Clear cached VPN credentials
4. Restart VPN client
5. Reset MFA
6. Re-test connection

---

##  Printer Offline
1. Check printer power & network
2. Restart printer
3. Clear print queue
4. Restart Print Spooler service
5. Remove & re-add printer
6. Print test page

---

##  Outlook Password Loop
1. Clear Credential Manager
2. Restart Outlook
3. Re-add account
4. Confirm Microsoft 365 license
5. Verify authentication sync

---

##  Slow PC
1. Check CPU/RAM/Disk usage
2. Disable startup apps
3. Clear temp files
4. Run updates
5. Reboot
6. Test performance

---

##  Shared Folder Access Denied
1. Verify user's identity
2. Check folder permissions
3. Confirm missing AD group membership
4. Add user to group
5. Force Group Policy update
6. Confirm access

---

These workflows provide documentation of how each issue was approached and resolved.
